<h4> The following can be used to insert an image of BLOB type into an
LogicSQL database.
</h4>
Note that (1) the table in the database is created by 
<pre>
      CREATE TABLE pictures (
            pic_id int,
	    pic_desc  varchar(100),
	    pic  BLOB,
	    primary key(pic_id)
      )
</pre>
(2) a unique constraint violation will be returned if the table
already contains a row with the same primary key value.
<p>
<hr>
Please input or select the path of the image!
<form name="upload-image" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data" action="servlet/UploadImageLogicSQL">
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>File path: </th>
    <td><input name="file-path" type="file" size="30" ></input></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td ALIGN=CENTER COLSPAN="2"><input type="submit" name=".submit" 
     value="Upload"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</form>
</body> 
